# =============================================================================
# PROJECT REGISTRY
# =============================================================================
# Copy this file to projects.env
# List all projects that should be connected to the logging infrastructure
#
# Format: Space-separated list of project names
# Each project name should match the prefix used in container names
#
# Example: If your containers are named:
#   - projecta-backend
#   - projecta-cron-fetch
#   - projectb-api
#   - projectb-worker
#
# Then your PROJECTS line should be:
#   PROJECTS="projecta projectb"
#
# The bootstrap.sh script will:
#   1. Create a Docker network for each project: {project}-net
#   2. Connect the Caddy container to each project network
#   3. This allows Caddy to reverse proxy to any container in any project

PROJECTS="projecta projectb"

# =============================================================================
# ADDING A NEW PROJECT
# =============================================================================
# 1. Add the project name to the PROJECTS list above
# 2. Run: ./bootstrap.sh
# 3. Add the corresponding syslog subdomain block to Caddyfile
# 4. Reload Caddy: docker exec system-caddy caddy reload --config /etc/caddy/Caddyfile
